Pre-Game Insights: Despite Guinea-Bissau's two clean sheets in qualifying, they are expected to struggle to prevent Egypt from scoring.
Egypt has kept consecutive clean sheets and aims to extend their ongoing unbeaten streak to four matches.
Guinea-Bissau's defense has been solid, but their offense struggles to find the net consistently.
Egypt's Mohamed Salah has not scored in three straight competitive games, while Trezeguet has scored their last four goals in qualifiers.
Hossam Hassan's Egypt seeks to increase their lead in Group A and maintain their unbeaten run.
